The Governor of Sokoto State, Hon. Aminu Waziri Tambuwal on Tuesday met with President Muhammadu Buhari at the Presidential Villa in Aso Rock, Abuja. Governor Tambuwal who met behind closed doors with the president declined to speak to State House correspondents on his mission to the seat of power. Tambuwal is one of the front runners for the opposition People’s Democratic Party’s (PDP) presidential ticket for the 2023 presidential general elections. Daily Independent reports that the meeting with President Buhari come days after the PDP’s consensus arrangements structured for four northern presidential aspirants failed. The PDP presidential aspirants involved in the arrangement included Governor Tambuwal, Governor Bala Mohammed of Bauchi State, former President of the Senate, Bukola Saraki, former Managing Director of FSB International Bank, Mohammed Hayatu-Deen.